Sticky sesame cauliflower and basmati brown rice

Follow @vegan.diet.ig for Daily vegan recipes 
Photo cred and recipe the_clumsy_vegan

Recipe:
Ingredients:
For baked cauliflower:
Cauliflower: 1 small head cut in bite sized pieces
Sesame oil: 1/2 Tbsp
Smoked salt: 2 Tsp
Garlic powder: 1tsp
For sauce: 
Sesame oil: 1/2 Tbsp
Xylitol: 1 Tbsp
Soya sauce: 2 1/2 Tbsp
Lemon: 1 tsp
Tomato paste: 1 1/2 Tbsp
Tahini: 1/2 Tbsp
Sugar free chilly sauce or Sriracha: 2 tsp
Arrowroot: 1 tsp
Other:
Spring onions: 3 finely chopped
Ginger: 1 Tbsp grated
Sesame oil: 1/2 Tbsp
Black sesame seeds: to garnish
Method:
1) Preheat oven 200C. Coat cauliflower with sesame oil, salt and garlic powder and roast in the oven for 15 minutes.
2)Start your sauce at 10 minutes into the oven. Mix all the ingredients listed under sauce in a bowl.
3) Heat sesame oil in a wok and add ginger and spring onions. Fry for a few seconds and add the sauce into the oil. Keep stirring as it will quickly begin to thicken. 
4) Take the florets out of the oven and drop them into in sauce. Mix to coat well. 
5) Garnish with sesame seeds and spring onions. Enjoy with rice.⠀⠀
